# Cursor Project Rules — sipdemo

## Agent Mode / Composer Loop Protocol

1. Prefer **Plan Mode** before non-trivial code changes. Track progress in `tasks/todo.md`.
2. Do **not** mark an issue solved until you run verification in the terminal and get **exit code 0**.
3. If an iteration fails, trace the failure from **raw** terminal output. Write lessons to `tasks/lessons.md`.
4. Use the Terminal tool automatically to build/test; do not claim tests passed without shell evidence.

## Core stack commands (Windows)

- Build: `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\build.ps1`
- Test: `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\test.ps1`
- Demo: `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\run-demo.ps1`
- CMake check target (after configure): `cmake --build build --config RelWithDebInfo --target check`

## Coding constraints

- C++17; match existing style in `include/sipdemo/` and `src/`.
- Keep SIP/RTP paths free of blocking on STT/Vosk (AI stays behind WebSocket).
- No new heavy dependencies without asking.
- Update `docs/ISSUES.md` or `docs/PERFORMANCE.md` when fixing a documented class of bug or adding a backlog item.

